verses.verse: Unto you lift I <S%H5375>up<s%> my <S%H5869>eyes<s%>, O you that <S%H3427>dwell<s%> in the <S%H8064>heavens<s%>.

<S%H5869>Behold<s%>, as the eyes of <S%H5650>servants<s%> look unto the <S%H3027>hand<s%> of their <S%H113>masters<s%>, and as the <S%H5869>eyes<s%> of a <S%H8198>maiden<s%> unto the <S%H3027>hand<s%> of her <S%H1404>mistress<s%>; so our <S%H5869>eyes<s%> wait upon the <S%H3068>Lord<s%> our <S%H430>God<s%>, until that he have mercy upon <S%H2603>us<s%>.
Have <S%H2603>mercy<s%> upon <S%H3068>us<s%>, O Lord, have <S%H2603>mercy<s%> upon <S%H7227>us<s%>: for we are exceedingly <S%H7646>filled<s%> with <S%H937>contempt<s%>.

Our <S%H5315>soul<s%> is <S%H7227>exceedingly<s%> <S%H7646>filled<s%> with the <S%H3933>scorning<s%> of those that are at <S%H7600>ease<s%>, and with the <S%H937>contempt<s%> of the <S%H1343>proud<s%>.
